                                                "useFigureAdditionalScale": false,
                                                "figureAdditionalScale": 1,
                                                "imgHeight": 300,
                                                "imgFit": "inside",
                                                "imgStretch": true,
                                                "hideFigureCaption": false,
                                                "hideFigureSubCaption": false,
                                                "hideFigureFootnote": false,
                                                "markdown": "The findings indicate that Zambia\u2019s ANC4 gaps stem primarily from efficiency and service continuity challenges rather than insufficient funding. Large performance differences across provinces with similar resources highlight the need to shift from input-based planning to performance-driven delivery, with stronger follow-up systems and systematic learning from high performers. By reducing service drop-offs and smoothing delivery across programmes, the health system can release operational efficiencies and reinvest these gains into ANC4 and other high-impact services, improving equity and outcomes without increasing overall expenditure."
                                            }
                                        }
                                    ]
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "cols",
                                    "id": "39f12781-62af-44ac-93e2-193dedc2c5c8",
                                    "children": [
                                        {
                                            "type": "item",
                                            "id": "64b9247f-2e3a-4b1d-92e6-83e4ecf0e594",
                                            "data": {
                                                "type": "text",
                                                "markdown": "\n\nRecommended Actions \n\nTo improve ANC4 coverage within existing resources, Zambia should shift toward performance-driven service delivery by scaling best practices from higher-performing provinces, strengthening follow-up through community health workers and appointment tracking, and reducing service drop-offs across the care pathway. Greater use of point-of-care diagnostics at primary care level\u2014including hemoglobin, syphilis, HIV, and blood pressure screening\u2014can replace costly centralized investigations, reduce delays, and keep women engaged in care. Aligning ANC outreach with immunization and under-five clinics will further minimize duplication and optimize staff time and transport. Efficiency gains from these measures should be reinvested into targeted ANC4 support, including transport assistance, community follow-up, and mobile services in low-performing districts.",
                                                "stretch": true,
                                                "fillArea": false,
                                                "textSize": 1,
                                                "textBackground": "none",
                                                "placeholderInvisible": false,
                                                "placeholderStretch": true,
                                                "placeholderHeight": 50,
                                                "useFigureAdditionalScale": false,
                                                "figureAdditionalScale": 1,
                                                "imgHeight": 300,
                                                "imgFit": "inside",
                                                "imgStretch": true,
                                                "hideFigureCaption": false,
                                                "hideFigureSubCaption": false,
                                                "hideFigureFootnote": false
                                            }
                                        }
                                    ]
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "cols",
                                    "id": "205ed83a-8053-460f-a93f-aab5d4ebf761",
                                    "children": [
                                        {
                                            "type": "item",
                                            "id": "c186e89b-75d7-42b7-a952-4e511bf7a210",
                                            "data": {
                                                "type": "text",
                                                "markdown": "Call to Action\n\nZambia has the capacity to close ANC4 gaps using existing resources\u2014what is needed now is decisive action to improve efficiency and service continuity. The Ministry of Health, in collaboration with the Ministry of Finance and partners, should prioritize performance-driven delivery, scale proven practices from high-performing provinces, and reinvest efficiency gains into targeted ANC4 support in low-performing districts. Acting now will accelerate progress on maternal and newborn outcomes, reduce geographic inequities, and ensure that every kwacha delivers measurable impact for women and children.",
                                                "stretch": true,
                                                "fillArea": false,
                                                "textSize": 1,
                                                "textBackground": "none",
                                                "placeholderInvisible": false,
                                                "placeholderStretch": true,
                                                "placeholderHeight": 50,
                                                "useFigureAdditionalScale": false,
