                                                "hideFigureCaption": false,
                                                "hideFigureSubCaption": false,
                                                "hideFigureFootnote": false,
                                                "markdown": "Measles delivery is strong overall, but uneven across months\u2014showing efficiency gains are possible without adding new funding.\nThe 25\u201330% drop between first and second doses is lost value that can be recovered through simple follow-up and community support.\n\nSmoothing delivery and improving dose completion reduces missed visits, repeat outreach, and emergency catch-up campaigns\u2014cutting transport, allowance, and logistics costs and freeing resources that can be redirected to strengthen ANC4.\n"
                                            }
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
