                                            "type": "item",
                                            "id": "fcfc566b-e7eb-4746-a727-9e6c20f4fe8d",
                                            "data": {
                                                "type": "text",
                                                "markdown": "Zambia can unlock fiscal space by reallocating resources from lower-impact or inefficient activities toward proven ANC demand-generation and service-delivery interventions. Priority efficiency actions include:\n\nSystematically identifying and scaling best practices from higher-performing provinces (including community follow-up models, facility scheduling approaches, and referral coordination mechanisms);\n\nStreamlining fragmented outreach and supervision activities to reduce duplication and administrative overhead;\n\nRedirecting savings toward high-return investments, such as community health worker incentives for ANC follow-up, transport vouchers for hard-to-reach populations, and optimized mobile clinic deployment.",
